	        <h3 id="1-content-page">
	            <a name="user-content-1-content-page" href="#1-content-page" class="headeranchor-link" aria-hidden="true">
	                <span class="headeranchor"></span>
	            </a>1. Content Page</h3>
	        <p>Content pages are the most widely used page across victoria.ac.nz, they will be suitable for nearly all of your content needs.</p>
	        <p>Content pages are made up of three main areas; left aside, main section, and right aside.</p>
	        <p>The main use of the left aside is for the left navigation menu, however it has a secondary use of containing important contact information.</p>
	        <p>The three areas have different behavior on mobile and desktop. The left and right asides are collapsed on mobile. This might dictate where you place content on the page, it’s important to have a strategy for your content.</p>
	        <h4 id="examples">
	            <a name="user-content-examples" href="#examples" class="headeranchor-link" aria-hidden="true">
	                <span class="headeranchor"></span>
	            </a>Examples:</h4>
	        <p>Your content might have some related links, though these links aren’t the main focus of your user need, they might be of interest as further reading. The right aside area would be an ideal place for these links.</p>
	        <p>Your main content might be to help users complete the task of filling out a form, you have important information the users need to know before completing the form successfully. Placing this content in the right aside will be usable on desktop however your mobile users will not see this content, therefore making it more difficult for users to complete the task.</p>
