	                <span class="headeranchor"></span>
	            </a>2. Section Page</h3>
	        <p>Section pages are considered task oriented way-finding pages.</p>
	        <p>What does that mean? We use these pages to direct users to the task they are looking to complete, whether that be finding out an answer to a question or to a page to fill out a form.</p>
	        <p>Section pages are made up of the left aside and the main section areas. The main section usually contains a header and promo area and three content columns.</p>

